KINO! Festival of German Films New York     | German | NYU                                                                                                                                                     Back to Previous Page         KINO! Festival of German Films New York     This year’s 39th edition of KINO! keeps delivering fresh German films to downtown New York. In its second year as an independent festival, KINO! will be presenting the latest of German cinema to a New York audience, in the beating heart of hip young Greenwich Village and in one of the city’s best-established arthouses - the Cinema Village in Manhattan. The festival will not only showcase ten feature-length films (four North American premieres and six East Coast premieres) and the German Short Film Night, but will also bring German filmmaker and actor guests who will talk about their work in panel discussions at Deutsches Haus at New York University (on the film The Lies of the Victors ) and the Goethe-Institut New York (on the film Beltracchi – The Art of Forgery ). As part of the festival, Deutsches Haus at NYU will present Die Lügen der Sieger: A Conversation between Christoph Hochhäusler and Amie Siegel , moderated by Professor Ulrich Baer, on April 11 at 4:30 p.m. More details about this event can be found here . The film selection, made by an independent expert jury consisting of Nicole Guillemet , former co-director of the Sundance Film Festival, Ian Stimler of the distributor Zeitgeist Films, and the journalist Karl Rozemeyer , shows us plenty of characters, who are struggling with a fight against powerful entities or with their own emotions, overcoming anxieties in a courageous, entertaining and sometimes even humorous way. This year’s films of KINO! are like emotional rollercoaster rides ending on life-affirming highs. Gripping thrillers, driven by young characters eager to make their mark on the world complete the wide-range line-up.  KINO! will kick off on April 9, 2015, with the East Coast premiere of the drama Tour De Force , presented by the director of the film, Christian Zübert , and run through April 16, 2015. North American premieres: Flights of Fancy (Hirngespinster) by Christian Bach The Lies of the Victors (Die Lügen der Sieger) by Christoph Hochhäusler The Pasta Detectives (Rico, Oscar und die Tieferschatten) by Neele Leana Vollmar Schmitke by Stepán Altrichter East Coast premieres: About a Girl (Charleen macht Schluss) by Mark Monheim Beltracchi – The Art of Forgery (Beltracchi – Die Kunst der Fälschung) by Arne Birkenstock The Kings Surrender (Wir waren Könige) by Philipp Leinemann To Life! (Auf das Leben!) by Uwe Janson Who Am I – No System is Safe (Who Am I – Kein System ist sicher) by Baran bo Odar Tour De Force (Hin und Weg) by Christian Zübert Apart from these films eight German short films will be shown at the German Short Film Night – Soirée Allemande .  More information on KINO! KINO! Festival of German Films New York     | German | NYU                                                                                                                                                     Back to Previous Page         KINO! Festival of German Films New York     This year’s 39th edition of KINO! keeps delivering fresh German films to downtown New York. In its second year as an independent festival, KINO! will be presenting the latest of German cinema to a New York audience, in the beating heart of hip young Greenwich Village and in one of the city’s best-established arthouses - the Cinema Village in Manhattan. The festival will not only showcase ten feature-length films (four North American premieres and six East Coast premieres) and the German Short Film Night, but will also bring German filmmaker and actor guests who will talk about their work in panel discussions at Deutsches Haus at New York University (on the film The Lies of the Victors ) and the Goethe-Institut New York (on the film Beltracchi – The Art of Forgery ). As part of the festival, Deutsches Haus at NYU will present Die Lügen der Sieger: A Conversation between Christoph Hochhäusler and Amie Siegel , moderated by Professor Ulrich Baer, on April 11 at 4:30 p.m. More details about this event can be found here . The film selection, made by an independent expert jury consisting of Nicole Guillemet , former co-director of the Sundance Film Festival, Ian Stimler of the distributor Zeitgeist Films, and the journalist Karl Rozemeyer , shows us plenty of characters, who are struggling with a fight against powerful entities or with their own emotions, overcoming anxieties in a courageous, entertaining and sometimes even humorous way. This year’s films of KINO! are like emotional rollercoaster rides ending on life-affirming highs. Gripping thrillers, driven by young characters eager to make their mark on the world complete the wide-range line-up.  KINO! will kick off on April 9, 2015, with the East Coast premiere of the drama Tour De Force , presented by the director of the film, Christian Zübert , and run through April 16, 2015. North American premieres: Flights of Fancy (Hirngespinster) by Christian Bach The Lies of the Victors (Die Lügen der Sieger) by Christoph Hochhäusler The Pasta Detectives (Rico, Oscar und die Tieferschatten) by Neele Leana Vollmar Schmitke by Stepán Altrichter East Coast premieres: About a Girl (Charleen macht Schluss) by Mark Monheim Beltracchi – The Art of Forgery (Beltracchi – Die Kunst der Fälschung) by Arne Birkenstock The Kings Surrender (Wir waren Könige) by Philipp Leinemann To Life! (Auf das Leben!) by Uwe Janson Who Am I – No System is Safe (Who Am I – Kein System ist sicher) by Baran bo Odar Tour De Force (Hin und Weg) by Christian Zübert Apart from these films eight German short films will be shown at the German Short Film Night – Soirée Allemande .  More information on KINO! Festival of German Films New York can be found here:   Website: www.kinofestivalnyc.com   Facebook: facebook.com/kinofestivalnyc  Twitter: @kinofestivalnyc KINO! 2015 is made possible through the generous contribution of the German Information Center , the Goethe-Institut New York , and Deutsches Haus at New York University and the media partnership with The Village Voice .
